This test verifies that M62-M68 can be remapped through NGC subroutines,
and that calling the original M-codes is supported in the remap subroutine.

(The classic test also had a Python-remap variant; gomc removed the embedded
Python interpreter, so only the NGC variant remains — the Python remap is a
genuine removal.)

The recursive call to the original functions needs supporting code for
mode 5 M-codes in `interp_convert.cc` `convert_m()`, and for M62-M68
in `rs274ngc_pre.cc`, `find_remappings()`.

The driver (test-ui.py) presents inputs on the motion I/O pins with halcmd,
issues the M62-M68 remaps via gmi MDI, and reads the resulting motion I/O pin
state back with halcmd.  See the `xfail` note: the NGC remaps run and M64/M65,
M66 and M68 pass; M62/M63/M67 (synchronised output followed by motion) diverge
on the documented milltask sync-I/O bug.
